Definition: disdainfully or ironically humorous
Example: scornful and mocking; his rebellion is the bitter, sardonic laughter of all great satirists- Frank Schoenberner; a wry pleasure to be...reminded of all that one is missing- Irwin Edman
Synonyms: snarky, disdainfully, or, ironically, humorous, scornful, and, mocking, his, rebellion, is, the, bitter, laughter, of, all, great, satirists, -, Frank, Schoenberner, a, wry, pleasure, to, be, reminded, that, one, missing, Irwin, Edman
Category: adj.all
